<TITLE> 3 four-party men held for 'buying votes' in Srimangal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moulavibazar, Dec 28 (bdnews24.com)  Police on Sunday detained three people in Srimangal for allegedly buying votes for a BNP-led four-party candidate. Local people held the three with a voter list of the area and Tk 30,000 from municipal area and turned them over to police, acting officer-in-charge of Srimangal Police Station Md Shahid Ullah said. In police interrogation, the captives confessed Shamim Ahmed, younger brother of four-party alliance candidate for Moulavibazar-4 constituency Mujibur Rahman, had given them Tk 40,000 to distribute among the voters. Police also confiscated a motorbike they were riding to dole out money. bdne
